    "body": "From stand-up discussion: I'm not wedded to a format. That Besu one is pleasant to me, but I don't use logz.io so have no idea what would work there. The important things are to (safely) enumerate any user-supplied (non-default) options and to summarise the running environment in some format.\r\n\r\nSome of the Besu output is just the default settings - that's not required imo.",
